  "commentary": "With SPX at 6596.37 sitting between massive negative gamma at 6590 (-10.6B) and positive gamma at 6605 (+15.0B), dealers are caught in a volatile squeeze where they must buy any dip toward 6590 and sell any push above 6605. The BREAKOUT regime with -766M total GEX means dealers are amplifying moves in both directions, but the proximity to these opposing gamma walls creates a narrow 15-point battleground. Watch for explosive moves if we clear either 6590 (accelerated selling) or 6605 (momentum buying through the wall), with 6610 as the next major resistance at +10.5B.\n\nBottom line: expect violent whipsaws in a tight 15-point range until one of these massive walls breaks.",
